@wendyinfutures I wrote a story about this a couple of years back. "Noon in the Antilibrary" projected a future in which whole Internets-worth of fake documentation, histories, videos etc. could be generated instantly. And now here we are! 

Welcome to the Antilibrary.
https://t.co/aJ048CyThZ

@Wiswell 1. "To a time traveler, we are all of us, all, always already dead."
2. 257 attempts to scuttle a ferry.
3. Attending every opera and symphony premiere in history.

@NikolasFuturist Tim Berners-Lee's pods, obviously, and other reversals of centralization tendencies.

Trustless systems.

More fun: nonverbal mixed reality. Unconscious nudges, symbols, soundscapes, immersions etc. to nudge us in some way.
